(truck horn blares)

00:37.170 --> 00:39.730
* In excelsis De...

00:39.770 --> 00:41.237
(music stops)

00:45.470 --> 00:47.472
(car alarm chirps)

00:56.250 --> 00:58.241
(phone ringing)

01:01.260 --> 01:03.080
Hi. What's going on?

01:03.130 --> 01:04.085
I'm following Damian.

01:04.130 --> 01:05.483
Good. You found something?

01:05.530 --> 01:07.395
Not with the Gerraghty family.

01:07.430 --> 01:08.749
I don't think
he's still working for them.

01:08.800 --> 01:09.698
But?

01:09.730 --> 01:11.789
He just pulled up
outside Florrick-Agos.

01:12.800 --> 01:14.233
DIANE:
To their building?

01:14.270 --> 01:15.259
Yeah.

01:15.300 --> 01:16.631
What do you think,
he's jumping ship?

01:16.670 --> 01:18.228
I have no idea.

01:18.270 --> 01:20.579
Okay, keep vetting him.

01:20.610 --> 01:22.498
Call me when you find out more.

01:25.350 --> 01:26.772
New York is really
coming together.

01:26.820 --> 01:28.242
I'm glad.

01:28.280 --> 01:30.214
You know where
your boy Damian is?

01:30.250 --> 01:31.387
My boy?

01:31.420 --> 01:33.149
You mean our newest partner?

01:33.190 --> 01:34.748
He's at Florrick-Agos.

01:34.790 --> 01:36.257
Why?

01:36.290 --> 01:37.382
I've no idea.

01:37.430 --> 01:39.625
But I guess you don't, either.

01:42.400 --> 01:44.163
DAMIAN:
Hello.

01:44.200 --> 01:45.360
Okay.

01:45.400 --> 01:47.891
Thanks, I'll try later.

01:47.940 --> 01:49.305
Yes?

01:49.340 --> 01:51.706
We have a meeting.
Damian Boyle.

01:51.740 --> 01:52.707
No.

01:52.740 --> 01:54.276
I have a meeting with David Lee.

01:54.310 --> 01:56.175
Yeah, David wanted
me to take it.

01:56.210 --> 01:58.872
He said, um, he'd "rather
negotiate with the Devil."

01:58.910 --> 02:01.447
Me, I don't care who I
negotiate with, so...

02:01.480 --> 02:02.583
Do you have my check?

02:02.620 --> 02:03.587
I do.

02:03.620 --> 02:08.410
$150,000. Your capital
contribution refunded.

02:10.560 --> 02:11.754
Nice furniture.

02:14.260 --> 02:15.852
May I see the check?
Yeah.

02:15.900 --> 02:19.233
Right after you sign
the exit contract

02:19.270 --> 02:20.737
from Lockhart-Gardner.

02:20.770 --> 02:23.307
Okay.

02:23.340 --> 02:25.160
Thanks.

02:25.210 --> 02:26.575
My pleasure.

02:29.710 --> 02:32.372
So, you're the
Governor's wife, yeah?

02:32.420 --> 02:33.512
Yup.

02:33.550 --> 02:34.710
Your husband's
the fella that

02:34.750 --> 02:36.308
slept with
all those prostitutes?

02:38.450 --> 02:39.553
Yes.

02:39.590 --> 02:40.659
Hey, I'm all for forgiveness.

02:40.690 --> 02:43.784
You know, confession-- best
thing God ever invented.

02:43.830 --> 02:45.354
Actually, I was talking
to me ma last night...

02:45.390 --> 02:46.596
Do you want me to read this?

02:46.630 --> 02:48.689
Yeah. Sorry.

02:48.730 --> 02:50.789
(knocking)

02:52.370 --> 02:54.395
Here. Something to play with.

02:56.410 --> 02:58.401
(indistinct chatter)

03:00.580 --> 03:01.831
What's the problem?

03:01.880 --> 03:03.541
The holiday party.

03:03.580 --> 03:05.445
Ah.

03:05.480 --> 03:08.517
Mr. Hayden,
could you do me a favor?

03:08.550 --> 03:10.347
Just look this over.

03:10.390 --> 03:12.381
It's my exit deal
from Lockhart-Gardner.

03:12.420 --> 03:14.456
Just_ see if there are
any hidden land mines.

03:14.490 --> 03:15.912
Certainly.
Thank you.

03:15.960 --> 03:16.984
Wait, wait. Let's bring
Alicia into this.

03:17.030 --> 03:20.397
We have sent out 800
invitations for Friday night,

03:20.430 --> 03:22.227
and we've gotten
30 yeses back.

03:22.270 --> 03:24.226
For the holiday party? 30 yeses?

03:24.270 --> 03:26.465
Yeah, we're trying
to figure out what to do.

03:26.500 --> 03:27.398
We didn't want to
ask you this,

03:27.440 --> 03:29.533
but... we need you to
invite your husband.

03:29.570 --> 03:31.606
Oh, come on, guys, we can't
keep going back to that well.

03:31.640 --> 03:34.404
If the governor comes, there
will be a jump in the RSVPs.

03:34.440 --> 03:36.408
Maybe people are
just late RSVPing.

03:36.450 --> 03:38.406
Let's just wait
another day.
No, the problem is

03:38.450 --> 03:40.372
another firm decided
to throw a party that night.

03:40.420 --> 03:42.388
Lockhart-Gardner?
Yeah.

03:42.420 --> 03:43.910
They're still trying
to starve us.
Okay.

03:43.950 --> 03:45.918
I'll make a call, but I'm not
promising anything.

03:45.950 --> 03:47.611
Okay, thank you.

03:47.660 --> 03:49.878
Who's...
Matthew Ashbaugh?

03:49.930 --> 03:51.420
What?

03:51.460 --> 03:52.688
Who's Matthew Ashbaugh?

03:52.730 --> 03:54.493
A... a client. Why?

03:54.530 --> 03:56.998
Special pains are
being made to segregate

03:57.030 --> 03:58.691
your interests from his.

04:00.840 --> 04:02.967
(classical music playing)
You can't get rid of me, Alicia.

04:03.010 --> 04:04.705
I'm always here.

04:04.740 --> 04:05.968
He's dead.

04:06.010 --> 04:07.671
Are his cases dead?

04:07.710 --> 04:09.507
I don't know.
Uh, some might be.

04:09.550 --> 04:12.872
Well, this contract attempts to
exclude you from any benefits.

04:14.650 --> 04:16.845
WOMAN: Hello?
ALICIA: Hello, Mrs. Ashbaugh,

04:16.890 --> 04:20.314
this is Alicia Florrick--
I don't know if you remember me.

04:20.360 --> 04:22.009
I used to represent
your husband.

04:23.630 --> 04:24.654
Hello?

04:24.690 --> 04:25.759
What do you want?

04:25.790 --> 04:28.020
Uh, is this a bad time?

04:28.060 --> 04:29.152
What do you want?

04:29.200 --> 04:33.489
Um, well, there are some cases,
y-your husband's cases,

04:33.540 --> 04:36.304
still unresolved, and I've since
left Lockhart-Gardner,

04:36.340 --> 04:40.333
and I was wondering if they were
settled to your satisfaction.

04:41.910 --> 04:43.741
You're not getting his money.

04:43.780 --> 04:45.805
I'm n... I'm not...
Um, what do you mean?

04:45.850 --> 04:48.842
There already is a will, and
if you make a big deal of this,

04:48.880 --> 04:51.610
I swear I'll sue you
for everything you have.

04:51.650 --> 04:54.380
(line clicks)

05:02.060 --> 05:04.062
ASHBAUGH:
You're not getting
paid enough, Alicia.

05:04.100 --> 05:05.795
Tell your friend
Will that.

05:05.830 --> 05:07.559
My friend?
Will.

05:07.600 --> 05:09.534
Gardner.
I thought you meant my will.

05:09.570 --> 05:10.969
Your... what?

05:11.010 --> 05:14.434
My last will and testament.

05:14.480 --> 05:15.936
You're a bit slow
today, aren't you?

05:15.980 --> 05:17.902
Mm. I think it's the music.

05:17.950 --> 05:20.009
Can we please
turn it down a little?

05:20.050 --> 05:22.917
And give the NSA a respite? No.

05:22.950 --> 05:25.748
If it's driving you crazy, just
think what it's doing to them.

05:25.790 --> 05:26.950
CLARKE:
Did you find out?

05:28.860 --> 05:30.452
About Matthew Ashbaugh.

05:30.490 --> 05:32.424
Oh, uh, not yet.

05:32.460 --> 05:34.826
I think it might have
something to do with his estate.

05:34.860 --> 05:36.589
That makes sense.
SONDRA:
Mrs. Florrick,

05:36.630 --> 05:39.098
your husband's
on the line.

05:39.130 --> 05:41.530
Robyn.

05:41.570 --> 05:43.060
Do me a favor.

05:43.110 --> 05:45.465
You see that man over there?

05:45.510 --> 05:48.001
Ask him if you can
record the negotiations.

05:48.040 --> 05:50.474
Tell him that you made a mistake
and you were supposed to

05:50.510 --> 05:52.410
do it from the beginning
and I'm mad at you.

05:52.450 --> 05:53.678
Cool.

05:55.950 --> 05:58.009
Peter, hi.
Is everything all right?

05:58.050 --> 06:00.109
No. Why did you wait
till today to invite me

06:00.160 --> 06:01.582
to your party on Friday?

06:03.590 --> 06:05.387
ALICIA:
It's a mistake.

06:05.430 --> 06:08.627
We've had some arguments around
here about imposing on you.

06:08.660 --> 06:09.888
Who called you?

06:09.930 --> 06:10.919
Nobody called me.

06:10.970 --> 06:12.858
It was an e-mail invite.

06:12.900 --> 06:14.094
By the way, it wasn't
an imposition.

06:14.140 --> 06:16.563
Although I do have to go to
dinner with my mother on Friday.

06:16.610 --> 06:17.702
Oh, okay, Peter,

06:17.740 --> 06:18.707
it's fine.

06:18.740 --> 06:19.832
No, listen, I really want to go.

06:19.880 --> 06:22.474
Mind ifI bring Mother along?
I think she'd love it.

06:24.080 --> 06:25.104
Jackie?

06:25.150 --> 06:27.448
Yeah. Can you call her?

06:27.480 --> 06:28.617
She doesn't think you like her.

06:28.650 --> 06:29.685
(chuckles)

06:29.720 --> 06:31.585
(chuckles) Okay.

06:31.620 --> 06:35.078
Uh, I got to go.
I'll see you on Friday.

06:35.120 --> 06:37.588
You can't agree to a party
without seeing the guest list.

06:37.630 --> 06:38.881
Oh, yes, I can.
I just did.

06:38.930 --> 06:40.022
No, Alicia represents
some clients

06:40.060 --> 06:42.563
you do not want to
end up in a photo with.

06:42.600 --> 06:43.567
It'll look bad.

06:43.600 --> 06:45.124
Eli, you do what you do.

06:45.170 --> 06:48.139
Okay? But I'm going to
my wife's holiday party.

06:48.170 --> 06:49.603
DAMIAN:
So, are we...

06:49.640 --> 06:51.460
are we signing
this, or what?

06:51.510 --> 06:52.738
Just a few questions.

06:52.780 --> 06:55.738
IfI sign this,
I get my capital contribution?

06:55.780 --> 06:56.576
Yes.

06:56.610 --> 06:58.771
And this contract
will have no impact

06:58.810 --> 07:00.949
on any profit participation

07:00.980 --> 07:03.084
earned during my employment
at Lockhart-Gardner?

07:03.120 --> 07:05.088
Uh, this contract has nothing
to do with profit participation.

07:05.120 --> 07:06.212
So, it will have no impact...

07:06.250 --> 07:08.718
That would follow.
It would follow
that this contract

07:08.760 --> 07:12.594
will have no impact...
of any profit participation

07:12.630 --> 07:14.928
during my time at
Lockhart-Gardner.

07:18.070 --> 07:20.038
No.

07:20.070 --> 07:21.230
Nice try.

07:21.270 --> 07:22.498
That's yours,
this is mine.

07:22.540 --> 07:23.507
What's wrong?

07:23.540 --> 07:25.167
Nothing's wrong.

07:25.210 --> 07:26.905
Very nice talking
to you, Robyn...

07:26.940 --> 07:28.578
and Alicia. Bye-bye.

07:29.950 --> 07:31.941
(whistles
Angels We Have Heard on High)

07:34.750 --> 07:37.583
That might be all we need.
Play it back.

07:37.620 --> 07:38.689
What?

07:38.720 --> 07:40.551
I had it on SmackTalk.

07:40.590 --> 07:42.524
DAMIAN (high-pitched):
So, are we... are we signing
this, or what?

07:42.560 --> 07:43.527
ALICIA:
Just a few questions.

07:43.560 --> 07:46.893
IfI sign this, I get
my capital contribution?

07:46.930 --> 07:47.828
DAMIAN:
Yes.

07:47.860 --> 07:49.725
Uh, my nephews,
they were playing with it.

07:49.770 --> 07:50.896
ALICIA (high-pitched):
...will have no impact

07:50.930 --> 07:52.636
on any profit
participation earned...

07:56.570 --> 07:57.798
So it will have no impact?

07:57.840 --> 07:59.705
It does that when you
push the farting button.

07:59.740 --> 08:00.832
And you pushed

08:00.880 --> 08:02.802
the farting button?
Not on purpose.

08:02.850 --> 08:04.943
...profit participation
dunng”.

08:04.980 --> 08:06.675
Mrs. Florrick?
ALICIA:
Yes?

08:06.720 --> 08:09.245
This is... a_ bit
of a surprise.

08:09.280 --> 08:11.009
Uh, you haven't signed
the exit contract?

08:11.050 --> 08:13.052
No, not yet. Why?

08:13.090 --> 08:14.955
I called an old acquaintance
in probate court

08:14.990 --> 08:16.958
about Mr. Ashbaugh's estate.

08:16.990 --> 08:18.287
A contending will

08:18.330 --> 08:20.059
has been discovered.

08:20.100 --> 08:21.795
Okay.
There were
two beneficiaries.

08:21.830 --> 08:23.525
The Smile Train, a charity.
* Angels we have heard on high

08:23.570 --> 08:25.561
It's been bequeathed
$12 million.

08:25.600 --> 08:27.693
* Sweetly singing
And you have been bequeathed

08:27.740 --> 08:29.605
the rest. _
* O'er the plains

08:29.640 --> 08:30.937
How much is the rest?

08:30.970 --> 08:32.574
* And the mountains in reply

08:32.610 --> 08:33.838
$12 million.

08:33.880 --> 08:36.098
* Echoing their joyful strains

08:36.140 --> 08:37.573
Holy s...

08:37.610 --> 08:45.016
* Gloria

08:45.050 --> 08:49.851
* In excelsis Deo.

08:58.870 --> 09:00.189
* Joy to the world

09:00.240 --> 09:02.561
* The Lord_ is _come
(phone rIngIng)

09:02.610 --> 09:06.159
* Let Earth receive
her king... *

09:06.210 --> 09:07.700
Hello?

09:07.740 --> 09:10.300
(ringing continues)
* Let every heart

09:10.350 --> 09:13.171
* Prepare him room

09:13.220 --> 09:15.313
* And heaven and nature sing

09:15.350 --> 09:18.888
* And heaven
and nature snng... *

09:20.320 --> 09:21.184
Hello?

09:21.220 --> 09:25.020
(laughing):
Oh, hello, Alicia, hello.

09:25.060 --> 09:27.620
I-I'm sorry, I have a phone now.

09:27.660 --> 09:29.025
It's very confusing.

09:29.060 --> 09:30.220
How are the kids?

09:30.270 --> 09:32.022
Great.
Jackie, actually...

09:32.070 --> 09:33.765
I wanted to invite you
to a party.

09:33.800 --> 09:35.097
A party?

09:35.140 --> 09:36.095
Really?

09:36.140 --> 09:37.107
Yes.

09:37.140 --> 09:38.368
Um, this Friday.

09:38.410 --> 09:40.037
For my law firm;
it's a holiday party.

09:40.080 --> 09:41.035
Oh, well,

09:41.080 --> 09:42.741
I'm honored, Alicia,

09:42.780 --> 09:44.702
but Peter and I
have dinner plans.

09:44.750 --> 09:45.944
I invited Peter, too.

09:45.980 --> 09:47.242
I would love it
if you both could come.

09:47.280 --> 09:48.918
How wonderful!

09:48.950 --> 09:51.043
Thank you, Alicia.

09:51.090 --> 09:52.853
Holiday decorations,
Jackie.

09:52.890 --> 09:54.755
Not Christmas,
not Jesus.

09:54.790 --> 09:56.348
Holiday.

09:56.390 --> 09:58.654
I have a Hanukkah, too.

09:58.690 --> 10:01.090
DAMIAN:
So...

10:01.130 --> 10:02.791
you're following me.

10:02.830 --> 10:04.695
Yeah.

10:04.870 --> 10:07.293
Will was worried why
I was at Florrick-Agos.

10:07.340 --> 10:10.002
I explained to him that
I was there negotiating

10:10.040 --> 10:11.359
Alic_ia Florrick's
eXIt package.

10:11.410 --> 10:13.105
Good to know.

10:13.140 --> 10:14.232
Maybe I can help you.

10:14.280 --> 10:15.975
What do you
need to know?

10:16.010 --> 10:18.376
How involved you are
with your old clients.

10:18.410 --> 10:19.775
I'm not involved.

10:19.820 --> 10:22.709
They're criminals,
and I'm a lavwer.

10:22.750 --> 10:24.115
Of course.

10:24.150 --> 10:25.310
Thanks.

10:25.350 --> 10:26.385
Hmm.

10:28.760 --> 10:31.388
ELI: Check out
the highlighted name.
What's this?

10:31.430 --> 10:33.250
This is the guest list for
Alicia Florrick's party.

10:33.300 --> 10:34.324
The one Peter
IS attending.

10:34.360 --> 10:36.248
MARILYN:
"Colin Sweeney..."

10:36.300 --> 10:37.392
Who...?

10:37.430 --> 10:39.125
Oh...
Yes.

10:39.170 --> 10:40.296
The wife-killer.

10:40.340 --> 10:42.160
The white O.J.

10:42.200 --> 10:43.167
One of Alicia's clients.

10:43.210 --> 10:44.700
Well, you should
tell Peter.

10:44.740 --> 10:45.707
I did.

10:45.740 --> 10:46.707
He's still going.

10:46.740 --> 10:48.002
Oh, that's unfortunate.

10:48.040 --> 10:49.439
Marilyn, you need
to tell him

10:49.480 --> 10:50.902
it's an ethics issue.

10:50.950 --> 10:53.874
It's not an ethics issue,
it's a publicity issue.

10:53.920 --> 10:54.944
That's not my business.

10:54.980 --> 10:56.015
But it's your
business that...

10:56.050 --> 10:57.881
(classical music playing softly)

10:57.920 --> 10:59.080
What is that?

10:59.120 --> 11:01.281
It's a pregnancy
sound system.

11:01.320 --> 11:02.821
It soothes the baby.

11:02.860 --> 11:04.782
The baby has to listen
to that all day?

11:04.830 --> 11:06.457
Eli, there are
no ethical issues here.

11:06.490 --> 11:10.199
Wait. When Peter
was state's attorney,

11:10.230 --> 11:11.993
he offered Sweeney a deal--

11:12.030 --> 11:14.066
early release in return
for wearing a wire.

11:14.100 --> 11:16.807
That's an_ ethics
Violation.

11:16.840 --> 11:20.071
Okay, but it's too late
to change Peter's mind.

11:20.110 --> 11:22.305
Once he says "no,"
he doesn't reverse himself.

11:22.340 --> 11:24.877
Then what?
Alicia.

11:24.910 --> 11:27.743
DUNAWAY: Okay, this
seems to be a matter

11:27.780 --> 11:28.815
of two wills.

11:28.850 --> 11:30.841
WILL: Yes, Your Honor.
Our client, Lila Ashbaugh,

11:30.890 --> 11:33.051
is the true beneficiary
of her husband's estate...

11:33.090 --> 11:34.182
Not after a second will
was discovered

11:34.220 --> 11:35.357
in a safety deposit box,
Your Honor.

11:35.390 --> 11:37.153
A will, we believe,
is invalid,

11:37.190 --> 11:38.885
and we ask _
for emergency relief.

11:38.930 --> 11:40.227
CARY: This second will was
drawn up one year later,

11:40.260 --> 11:42.399
and 16 months
before Mr. Ashbaugh died.

11:42.430 --> 11:45.763
Yes, but it was drawn up
in Magic Marker.

11:45.800 --> 11:47.438
It could be drawn up in crayon.
It's still valid...

11:47.470 --> 11:48.494
Could have been, but it was
drawn up in Magic Marker...

11:48.540 --> 11:50.030
You should know that.
It's still valid, Mr. Gardner.

11:50.070 --> 11:50.968
Ladies, gentlemen, yes, I know.

11:51.010 --> 11:53.228
I know. Other judges
let their lawyers run

11:53.280 --> 11:55.874
free and wild,
but in my court,

11:55.910 --> 11:59.744
my probate court,
where I have been assigned,

11:59.780 --> 12:01.111
you will bridle yourselves.

12:01.150 --> 12:03.084
Now, one will bequeaths

12:03.120 --> 12:06.385
the $24 million in personal
property to Mrs. Ashbaugh.

12:06.420 --> 12:08.809
And the other will...
The later will.

12:08.860 --> 12:09.827
The other will,

12:09.860 --> 12:11.851
uh, bequeaths the assets

12:11.890 --> 12:14.791
to the Smile Train charity
and...

12:14.830 --> 12:17.469
Alicia Florrick.

12:17.500 --> 12:19.798
Well, hello, Ms. Florrick.

12:19.840 --> 12:20.932
Your Honor.

12:20.970 --> 12:22.232
It seems to be
your luclq day.

12:22.270 --> 12:23.259
The wife of
a governor

12:23.310 --> 12:25.733
and a $12 million inheritance.

12:27.510 --> 12:29.375
Well, it's an odd day anyway.

12:29.410 --> 12:31.947
Now, it seems to be our duty

12:31.980 --> 12:35.848
to decide which will is valid,
is that correct?

12:35.880 --> 12:37.416
