(classical music
playing quietly)
ELI: What?

25:34.830 --> 25:35.990
Do you hear that?

25:37.100 --> 25:39.625
It's my pregnancy sound system.

25:39.670 --> 25:41.331
It soothes the baby.

25:41.370 --> 25:44.066
He doesn't like Chopin very
much, but he really, really...
Alicia,

25:44.110 --> 25:46.135
will you speak to Sweeney?

25:46.170 --> 25:47.831
No.

25:47.880 --> 25:48.869
You won't? Why not?

25:48.910 --> 25:51.071
Because I won't
disinvite a client.

25:51.110 --> 25:52.839
Alicia, this is
not a small issue.
I know.

25:52.880 --> 25:53.949
You should tell Peter.

25:53.980 --> 25:55.709
And my guess is
you already told Peter

25:55.750 --> 25:57.308
and he's coming aanay.

25:57.350 --> 26:00.217
But I'm not disinviting
a guest.

26:00.250 --> 26:02.650
(siren whoops)

26:06.960 --> 26:09.724
So, uh, what's the plan?

26:09.760 --> 26:10.966
(indistinct radio chatter)

26:11.000 --> 26:12.069
My plan?

26:12.100 --> 26:13.260
Reading.

26:13.300 --> 26:14.836
For how long?

26:14.870 --> 26:16.735
See that bus back there?

26:16.770 --> 26:19.204
Takes arrestees to court
for their bond hearings.

26:19.240 --> 26:21.379
And you're waiting
till it leaves?

26:21.410 --> 26:22.308
Yup.

26:22.340 --> 26:24.877
So I'm gonna be stuck
in holding overnight?

26:24.910 --> 26:26.844
Yup.

26:26.880 --> 26:28.177
Because Damian asked you to?

26:28.220 --> 26:29.619
Yup.

26:29.650 --> 26:30.719
Why?

26:30.750 --> 26:31.842
Because I owe him.

26:31.890 --> 26:33.084
What do you owe him?

26:34.790 --> 26:37.179
Wow. You can't turn it off,
can you?

26:37.220 --> 26:40.155
Just stop being an investigator
for, like, ten minutes.

26:40.190 --> 26:41.623
Will that help me?

26:41.660 --> 26:42.649
Sure.

26:42.700 --> 26:45.089
Okay.

26:45.130 --> 26:46.358
Charm me.

26:46.400 --> 26:47.958
What?

26:48.000 --> 26:50.161
You want out of your cuffs?

26:50.200 --> 26:51.633
Turn on the charm.

26:51.670 --> 26:52.807
I don't do charm.

26:52.840 --> 26:54.330
Okay, then sit tight.

26:57.210 --> 26:59.349
What do you call
a boomerang

26:59.380 --> 27:01.712
that doesn't come back?

27:01.750 --> 27:04.116
What?

27:04.150 --> 27:05.742
A stick.

27:29.410 --> 27:31.799
Mrs. Florrick,

27:31.850 --> 27:35.308
how long have you been
Mr. Ashbaugh's attorney?

27:35.350 --> 27:36.908
Around two years.

27:36.950 --> 27:38.247
Right up until his death.

27:41.160 --> 27:42.957
And in all that time,

27:42.990 --> 27:46.357
did Mr. Ashbaugh ever threaten
to fire you as his attorney?

27:46.390 --> 27:47.721
No, not to my knowledge.

27:47.760 --> 27:49.250
Really?

27:49.300 --> 27:50.892
Are you certain of that?

27:50.930 --> 27:52.898
Well...

27:52.930 --> 27:54.898
I'm not certain of anything.

27:54.940 --> 27:57.090
(chuckles)

27:57.140 --> 27:59.904
But if Mr. Gardner has
something more specific

27:59.940 --> 28:02.738
he'd like to ask.

28:08.280 --> 28:10.840
And in all that time,

28:10.890 --> 28:14.109
did Mr. Ashbaugh ever threaten
to fire you as his attorney?

28:14.160 --> 28:17.755
No, I mean...

28:17.790 --> 28:21.396
are you talking about the thing
two years ago?

28:21.430 --> 28:23.990
Yes, the "thing"
two years ago.

28:24.030 --> 28:25.292
Tell me about this...

28:26.770 --> 28:29.034
(grunts)

28:29.070 --> 28:31.061
Hmm.

28:36.040 --> 28:39.407
Did Mr. Ashbaugh express worries
about your representation

28:39.450 --> 28:41.418
in a meeting
in his New York apartment

28:41.450 --> 28:44.089
on September 23, 2011?

28:46.190 --> 28:48.055
They're out to get me.
Matthew, if you say that

28:48.090 --> 28:49.409
in this deposition,
it will sound crazy.

28:49.460 --> 28:51.052
If I don't say
in this deposition,

28:51.090 --> 28:52.318
then they'll get away with it.

28:52.360 --> 28:53.327
I have enemies.

28:53.360 --> 28:55.294
Yes, and your enemies will cheer
if you say this.

28:55.330 --> 28:57.025
Trust me, Matthew, please.

28:57.060 --> 28:58.493
Stop saying my name like that.

28:58.530 --> 29:00.418
I'm not 12 years old.

29:00.470 --> 29:02.893
Yes, sir, I...

29:02.940 --> 29:04.362
Matthew.

29:04.410 --> 29:05.900
Listen to me.

29:05.940 --> 29:09.432
You're a smart _man _
whose words are ea5ily tmsted.

29:09.480 --> 29:10.947
People don't see
as deeply as you do.

29:10.980 --> 29:12.208
And they'll use
the surface of your words...

29:12.250 --> 29:13.444
Stop it, Alicia.

29:13.480 --> 29:15.812
Are you married or aren't you?

29:17.350 --> 29:19.284
Are you married, Alicia?

29:25.990 --> 29:28.925
And after he asked you that,
did he threaten to fire you?

29:28.960 --> 29:30.928
Yes.

29:30.970 --> 29:32.426
And why did he threaten that?

29:32.470 --> 29:34.131
I don't know.

29:34.170 --> 29:35.797
But later that night,
didn't you say

29:35.840 --> 29:37.364
that Mr. Ashbaugh was
in love with you?

29:43.040 --> 29:45.873
Do you want me to
repeat the question?

29:45.910 --> 29:47.912
No.

29:50.890 --> 29:52.949
I was joking when I said that.

29:52.990 --> 29:55.083
You were joking
that Mr. Ashbaugh was

29:55.120 --> 29:57.213
in love with you and would
do anything you asked?

29:57.260 --> 29:59.251
You're saying that was a joke?

30:02.930 --> 30:04.591
Don't worry, I can get him
to change his mind.

30:04.630 --> 30:06.825
How?

30:06.870 --> 30:08.428
He cares about me.

30:08.470 --> 30:10.904
You've got him wrapped around
your finger, is that it?

30:10.940 --> 30:12.965
(laughs)

30:13.010 --> 30:15.001
I have my ways.

30:34.400 --> 30:37.289
*

30:48.610 --> 30:51.374
_ _ WILL: _
This is crazy romantic.

30:51.410 --> 30:54.311
(laughs)

30:54.350 --> 30:57.410
(church bell tolling
in distance)

30:57.450 --> 31:00.112
This is the happiest
I've ever been.

31:07.260 --> 31:10.229
Mrs. Florrick, you knew he was
in love with you,

31:10.260 --> 31:13.263
and you used it to get your way?

31:17.600 --> 31:20.501
May I remind you
that you are under oath?

31:21.510 --> 31:24.308
I didn't intentionally use him.

31:24.350 --> 31:26.944
Not intentionally?
I see.

31:26.980 --> 31:29.039
So it's just the way
you are with men?

31:30.220 --> 31:33.986
No.

31:34.020 --> 31:35.419
I cared for him.

31:35.460 --> 31:36.552
I liked him.

31:36.590 --> 31:39.457
And so it was all right
to use him?

31:39.490 --> 31:42.220
You make things sound so simple.

31:45.330 --> 31:46.558
I'm married.

31:46.600 --> 31:48.431
You always use that, don't you?

31:48.470 --> 31:50.495
"Married."

31:50.540 --> 31:52.235
You're conveniently married
when you want to be.

31:52.270 --> 31:54.670
That's not fair.

31:54.710 --> 31:56.439
I loved you.

31:56.480 --> 31:58.277
You made me believe that

31:58.310 --> 32:00.175
so that you could steal
my clients.

32:00.210 --> 32:02.212
No.

32:03.080 --> 32:04.616
Will.

32:06.220 --> 32:07.710
Stop it!

32:07.750 --> 32:09.650
I don't like it
when you're weak.

32:21.370 --> 32:23.429
Come back to bed.

32:23.470 --> 32:24.960
You're working too hard.

32:25.010 --> 32:28.639
And I have
a tough Witness tomorrow.

32:28.680 --> 32:30.739
Let it go.

32:30.780 --> 32:33.749
I'm here now.

32:33.780 --> 32:35.975
(chuckles)

32:43.790 --> 32:45.121
Good news.
Donna Bra2ile wants to meet.

32:45.160 --> 32:47.151
Why?
Why do you think?

32:47.190 --> 32:48.327
2016.

32:48.360 --> 32:49.452
(chuckles) No.
Yes.

32:49.500 --> 32:52.367
Peter, it's not just the
presidency they're looking for.

32:52.400 --> 32:53.628
It's the vice presidency.

32:53.670 --> 32:54.989
Biden won't be Hillary's.

32:55.040 --> 32:56.393
Hillary won't be Biden's.

32:56.440 --> 32:57.759
They're looking for new talent.

32:57.800 --> 32:59.506
Or a stalking horse.
So? The horse goes lame.

32:59.540 --> 33:01.508
The stalking horse
becomes the horse.

33:01.540 --> 33:03.576
Who's the horse?
I don't know,
Whatever you meant.

33:03.610 --> 33:04.599
The point is,
she wants to meet.

33:04.650 --> 33:05.742
Great. When?

33:05.780 --> 33:07.008
That's the problem.

33:07.050 --> 33:08.642
She's in town
this Friday.

33:08.680 --> 33:10.045
During Alicia's party.

33:10.080 --> 33:11.616
Eli, you know
that I want...
I know.

33:11.650 --> 33:12.617
I know.
But she'll understand.

33:12.650 --> 33:13.742
Alicia will understand.

33:13.790 --> 33:16.350
This is about
your future, Peter.

33:19.060 --> 33:21.699
You're not trying to pull
something over on me, are you?

33:23.500 --> 33:25.525
Yes, I'm arranging
a meeting with Donna Brazile

33:25.570 --> 33:27.390
to keep you from going
to Alicia's party.

33:27.430 --> 33:28.738
That makes sense.

33:28.770 --> 33:30.738
(laughs)
(sighs)

33:30.770 --> 33:33.238
You want me to call
AllCla and cancel?

33:33.270 --> 33:35.579
No, I'll do it.

33:39.510 --> 33:42.149
TV ANNOUNCER:
...and the fans are on fire,

33:42.180 --> 33:43.613
because they've
just witnessed history.

33:43.650 --> 33:45.641
(laughs)

33:48.660 --> 33:50.252
Used to be
a beat cop?

33:50.290 --> 33:51.826
Uh, yeah.

33:51.860 --> 33:53.225
For five years.

33:53.260 --> 33:55.797
Still got the
holster scars?

33:55.830 --> 33:57.127
Both hips.

33:57.160 --> 33:58.764
You like your Bersa?

33:59.730 --> 34:00.822
My BP9?

34:00.870 --> 34:02.428
Yeah.

34:02.470 --> 34:03.437
It's light.

34:03.470 --> 34:05.461
It's like a kid's toy.

34:06.840 --> 34:09.308
You should try
the Smith & Wesson M&P.

34:09.340 --> 34:10.432
Same size.

34:10.480 --> 34:12.698
Mmm, I never liked the grip.

34:12.750 --> 34:14.479
(TV announcer
continues indistinctly)

34:16.220 --> 34:19.439
You want to find out
about Damian, don't you?

34:19.490 --> 34:20.616
That's why you're here.

34:23.290 --> 34:24.518
Yeah.

34:31.730 --> 34:34.767
It's too bad I like Damian
more than I like you.

34:36.800 --> 34:39.064
Well, wait till you
get to know me better.

34:43.540 --> 34:45.849
* Silent night

34:45.880 --> 34:46.972
No, no.

34:47.010 --> 34:49.740
Alicia, I'm very excited
to come to your holiday party.

34:49.780 --> 34:51.611
ALICIA:
Jackie, I'm heading
into court right now.

34:51.650 --> 34:53.811
What can I help you with?

34:53.850 --> 34:55.386
Well, I was talking
to your mother,

34:55.420 --> 34:57.615
and she said she was
bringing a guest,

34:57.660 --> 35:00.686
and I would love
to bring a friend.

35:02.730 --> 35:04.493
Let me take it.

35:04.530 --> 35:06.521
No, I'm-I'm good.

35:19.250 --> 35:20.342
Good morning, Mrs. Florrick.

35:20.380 --> 35:22.268
Good morning to you.

35:22.320 --> 35:25.414
How long have you been
Mr. Ashbaugh's attorney?

35:25.450 --> 35:27.884
Oh, about two years.

35:27.920 --> 35:29.911
And did Mr. Ashbaugh ever
threaten to fire you

35:29.960 --> 35:31.780
as his attorney
over those two years?

35:31.830 --> 35:33.149
Yes.

35:35.500 --> 35:36.455
And when was this?

35:36.500 --> 35:39.219
September 23, 2011.

35:40.530 --> 35:41.895
Could you explain
the circumstances?

35:41.940 --> 35:42.895
Yes.

35:42.940 --> 35:46.432
You and I were at his apartment
in New York City

35:46.470 --> 35:48.529
prepping him for his testimony.

35:48.580 --> 35:50.172
And was there anything
about that night...

35:50.210 --> 35:51.199
Actually,
I wasn't finished.

35:52.310 --> 35:53.743
Do you want me to finish?

35:55.580 --> 35:56.547
Please.

35:56.580 --> 35:57.717
ALICIA:
He was being removed

35:57.750 --> 35:59.183
from the board of

35:59.220 --> 36:00.949
one of the companies
he had created.

36:00.990 --> 36:04.323
Mr. Ashbaugh thought that
he should be allowed to testify

36:04.360 --> 36:07.420
to some of the concerns
he had over the board members.

36:07.460 --> 36:10.657
We argued that was not
essential to the facts.

36:10.700 --> 36:12.395
And did you
change his mind?

36:13.430 --> 36:14.863
Yes, I did.

36:27.610 --> 36:30.738
And did you claim that Mr.
Ashbaugh was in love with you?

36:37.560 --> 36:39.482
Mrs. Florrick?

36:42.800 --> 36:44.722
I did claim that.

36:44.770 --> 36:46.761
And did you suggest that you...

36:49.440 --> 36:51.704
...could use his love to...

36:54.910 --> 36:56.377
...manipulate him?

36:59.710 --> 37:01.610
I said it was a possibility.

37:01.650 --> 37:03.015
And did you
manipulate him

37:03.050 --> 37:05.518
into signing off on his will?

37:07.550 --> 37:08.482
Yes.
CARY:
Your Honor.

37:08.520 --> 37:10.954
May I have a minute
to consult with my client?

37:10.990 --> 37:11.957
No, Counselor.

37:11.990 --> 37:13.719
I think she's doing fine.

37:13.760 --> 37:14.749
Conﬁnue.

37:16.900 --> 37:18.629
WILL:
And this manipulation,

37:18.670 --> 37:21.389
in your opinion, did it
constitute undue influence?

37:21.440 --> 37:23.897
Unfortunately, I think it did.

37:23.940 --> 37:25.999
WILL:
And was there
anyone else

37:26.040 --> 37:27.803
involved with this
manipulation?

37:27.840 --> 37:28.829
ALICIA:
Yes.

37:28.880 --> 37:30.939
There was?

37:30.980 --> 37:31.969
VVho?

37:34.080 --> 37:35.638
David Lee.

37:37.680 --> 37:41.719
David Lee was involved
with this will?

37:41.760 --> 37:43.648
No.

37:43.690 --> 37:45.521
The other one.

37:49.760 --> 37:51.057
Thank you, Mrs. Florrick.

37:51.100 --> 37:52.522
Whoa, wait a minute.

37:52.570 --> 37:54.060
I don't think
Mrs. Florrick was finished.

37:54.100 --> 37:55.590
No, I don't think
she was, either.

37:55.640 --> 37:57.790
What-What do you mean
by "the other one"?

37:57.840 --> 37:59.398
Do you mean
the other will?

37:59.440 --> 38:00.862
Yes.
David Lee is

38:00.910 --> 38:03.037
Lockhart-Gardner's lawyer
in family law.

38:03.080 --> 38:06.379
He asked me to use my influence

38:06.410 --> 38:09.675
with Mr. Ashbaugh
to get him to sign this will.

38:09.720 --> 38:12.609
DUNAWAY:
You mean the will
benefitting Mrs. Ashbaugh.

38:12.650 --> 38:13.617
ALICIA:
Yes.

38:13.650 --> 38:15.618
Mr. Ashbaugh
was delaying.

38:15.660 --> 38:18.049
Mr. Lee asked me to...

38:18.090 --> 38:21.651
"prime the pump,"
I believe were his words.

38:21.700 --> 38:23.429
DUNAWAY:
Okay.

38:23.460 --> 38:26.759
Anything further,
Counselor?

38:30.600 --> 38:32.033
Not for the moment.

38:39.910 --> 38:43.346
You know, Eli thinks
that this is about 2016.

38:43.380 --> 38:44.608
Is he right?

38:44.650 --> 38:46.845
Well, he's partially right.

38:46.890 --> 38:48.687
We're gonna see
Who's suiting up

38:48.720 --> 38:49.914
and Who's sitting
on the sidelines.

38:49.960 --> 38:50.813
ELI:
Well, we're...

38:50.860 --> 38:54.079
W-Would you like us
to be suiting up?

38:54.130 --> 38:55.097
BRAZILE:
Well, it depends.

38:55.130 --> 38:56.722
Would you consider?

38:56.760 --> 38:58.022
(phone ringing)
Oh.

38:58.060 --> 38:59.027
Excuse me.

38:59.070 --> 39:00.799
Go ahead,
take it.

39:00.830 --> 39:01.990
Um...

39:02.040 --> 39:02.995
it's my mom.

39:03.040 --> 39:05.600
Well, now you
have to take it.

39:05.640 --> 39:06.868
No. No, he really doesn't.
Come on.

39:06.910 --> 39:08.537
It's his mom, Eli.

39:08.580 --> 39:09.535
Thanks, Donna.

39:09.580 --> 39:10.729
Hi, Mom.

39:10.780 --> 39:13.840
Uh... no, I'm sorry,
I can't make it.

39:13.880 --> 39:15.017
I'm in a meeting.

39:15.050 --> 39:16.938
Sorry.

39:16.980 --> 39:18.379
Yeah.

39:18.420 --> 39:19.682
All right.

39:19.720 --> 39:20.687
Good-bye.

39:20.720 --> 39:22.017
Do you have
to be someplace?

39:22.060 --> 39:23.152
No. No, we're just...

39:23.190 --> 39:24.157
PETER:
Actually, yes.

39:24.190 --> 39:25.782
My Wife's party.

39:25.830 --> 39:27.422
But I've occupied your time.

39:30.200 --> 39:32.794
Donna...

39:32.830 --> 39:34.832
do you want to go
to a party?

39:36.540 --> 39:38.565
Those are
magical words.

39:38.610 --> 39:40.532
(Peter and Donna laughing)

39:40.570 --> 39:42.071
* Jingle bells, jingle bells

39:42.110 --> 39:43.509
* Jingle all the way...

39:43.540 --> 39:45.770
ALICIA:
I can't hear you. Hello?

39:45.810 --> 39:46.970
ELI:
Yes, Alicia.

39:47.010 --> 39:48.773
Alicia, we're...
we're coming now.

39:48.820 --> 39:49.946
To your party.

39:49.980 --> 39:50.742
Eli?

39:50.780 --> 39:53.089
Yes. We are coming
to your party.

39:53.120 --> 39:54.815
Peter and... Donna Brazile.

39:54.860 --> 39:56.111
Did... did you just say

39:56.160 --> 39:57.980
Donna Brazile is coming
to my party?

39:58.020 --> 39:59.055
Yes. Yes, I know.

39:59.090 --> 40:00.227
We have lost
all shreds of sanity.

40:00.260 --> 40:02.558
(conversing indistinctly)
But I just wanted to know...

40:02.600 --> 40:05.125
please, God...
is Colin Sweeney there?

40:05.170 --> 40:06.865
Be of good cheer, Eli.

40:06.900 --> 40:08.197
Colin Sweeney couldn't make it.

40:08.230 --> 40:09.959
His flight got delayed
in San Francisco.

40:10.000 --> 40:11.900
Oh, thank God!

40:11.940 --> 40:14.602
Thank your Christian Jesus God.

40:14.640 --> 40:15.709
Merry Christmas, Eli.

40:15.740 --> 40:16.968
* Jingle bells...

40:17.010 --> 40:18.477
So, are we
millionaires yet?

40:18.510 --> 40:20.205
Only in the love
we have for each other.

40:20.250 --> 40:21.945
Can we buy anything
with that?

40:21.980 --> 40:23.675
Well, you can always...

40:23.720 --> 40:24.687
Uh-oh.

40:24.720 --> 40:26.938
What?

40:26.990 --> 40:28.082
Eli's not gonna
be happy.

40:28.120 --> 40:30.088
GRACE:
Why? Who is it?

40:30.120 --> 40:31.451
ALICIA:
An old client.

40:31.490 --> 40:33.151
Lemond Bishop.

40:33.190 --> 40:35.454
The top drug dealer in Chicago.

40:37.500 --> 40:38.899
Sometimes I think
of you as Mom,

40:38.930 --> 40:40.591
and other times just as
this interesting person

40:40.630 --> 40:41.699
who lives at our house.

40:41.740 --> 40:43.731
Be right back.

40:43.770 --> 40:45.067
Excuse me.

40:45.110 --> 40:46.099
Cary!

40:46.140 --> 40:47.630
What's Lemond Bishop
doing here?

40:47.670 --> 40:49.638
Oh, he came?
That's great. Where?

40:49.680 --> 40:50.977
You invited him?
ROBYN:
No, I did.

40:51.010 --> 40:53.444
I thought you wanted
him as a client.

40:54.920 --> 40:56.171
Oh, God.

40:56.220 --> 40:57.642
Because we don't
actually have

40:57.680 --> 40:59.739
a national religion
in America, Jackie.

40:59.790 --> 41:02.884
That should have no impact
on office decorations.

41:02.920 --> 41:04.922
Out of sensitivity.

41:04.960 --> 41:06.552
Veronica, I don't want
to offend you, but

41:06.590 --> 41:08.558
you really should think
about drinking less.

41:08.600 --> 41:09.692
Oh, really? Why is that?

41:09.730 --> 41:10.958
'Cause you're
raising your voice.

41:11.000 --> 41:12.262
Well, maybe you should
drink a little more,

41:12.300 --> 41:14.029
and that might kill
that bug up your ass.

41:14.070 --> 41:16.061
Could you deal with that?

41:16.100 --> 41:17.067
Thanks.

41:17.100 --> 41:18.465
(phone ringing)

41:20.770 --> 41:22.237
Florrick-Agos & Associates.

41:22.280 --> 41:25.579
Oh. I expected to get Cary.

41:27.250 --> 41:28.877
I'll have him call you back.

41:28.920 --> 41:30.148
No, that's all right.

41:30.180 --> 41:31.784
Uh, there's been a...

41:31.820 --> 41:33.811
Something's happened.

41:33.850 --> 41:36.683
We discovered another
safety-deposit box

41:36.720 --> 41:38.085
belonging to Mr. Ashbaugh.

41:38.120 --> 41:41.157
Okay.

41:41.190 --> 41:43.021
There were four
more Wills in it,

41:43.060 --> 41:45.824
leaving all his money
to four other women.

41:45.870 --> 41:49.658
This seems to be something
Ashbaugh does.

41:49.700 --> 41:50.689
Did.

41:55.780 --> 41:59.671
So it looks like all five
will be found invalid.

41:59.710 --> 42:02.645
Anything else?

42:04.280 --> 42:05.281
No.

42:05.320 --> 42:08.653
Well, thanks for calling.

42:08.690 --> 42:11.284
You're welcome.

42:11.320 --> 42:12.651
Happy holidays.

42:14.360 --> 42:20.196
* In a one-horse open sleigh.

42:20.230 --> 42:22.960
(guests applauding)

42:24.240 --> 42:25.730
I usually vote
Republican,

42:25.770 --> 42:27.761
but I couldn't resist
voting for you.

42:27.810 --> 42:30.074
Yeah, uh, here,
let's find Alicia. Donna...

42:30.110 --> 42:31.668
I-I would love some time
to talk to you, sir.

42:31.710 --> 42:32.779
About some
charity ideas.

42:32.810 --> 42:33.947
Sounds good.

42:33.980 --> 42:35.675
Hey, Cary,
congratulations.

42:35.720 --> 42:36.812
Is that who
I think it was?

42:36.850 --> 42:37.976
Yeah, just keep moving.

42:38.020 --> 42:39.817
Donna, I'd like you
to meet Alicia.

42:39.850 --> 42:40.942
Lemond friggin' Bishop?

42:40.990 --> 42:42.651
It was news
to me, too, Eli.

42:42.690 --> 42:44.351
PETER:
Hey.

42:44.390 --> 42:45.254
This is terrific.

42:45.290 --> 42:47.349
Thank you for coming.

42:47.390 --> 42:48.857
Donna, I'd like you
to meet my Wife Alicia.

42:48.900 --> 42:49.798
Pleasure to meet you.

42:49.830 --> 42:51.866
Likewise.
Thank you so much for coming.

42:51.900 --> 42:53.959
Something strong.

42:56.000 --> 42:59.106
Is that music coming
from your stomach?

42:59.140 --> 43:00.232
Yes.

43:00.270 --> 43:00.964
It's my music system
for the baby.

43:01.010 --> 43:02.637
Oh, how clever.

43:02.680 --> 43:03.977
How many months?

43:04.010 --> 43:05.079
MARILYN:
Three and a half.

43:05.110 --> 43:06.702
VERONICA: And do you
know the sex yet?

43:06.750 --> 43:07.899
MARILYN:
I do. It's a boy.

43:07.950 --> 43:09.679
Oh, a boy.

43:09.720 --> 43:10.778
How sweet.

43:10.820 --> 43:11.787
I love boys.

43:11.820 --> 43:13.219
Do you have a name yet?

43:13.250 --> 43:14.239
I do.

43:14.290 --> 43:15.689
Peter.

